gov.usda.DataCatalogClient

Class Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usda.DataCatalogClient.Client

  • public class Client
extends java.lang.Object
    The Client class is used for interacting with a CKAN instance where Project Open Data attributes have been added to the extra field. Create Dataset To create a dataset, use method @see public void createDataset(Dataset ds). This method takes in a Project Open Data compliant dataset and imports it into CKAN. Read Full Catalog This class offers a method to compile a catalog from multiple CKAN organizations.
    Author:
    bbrotsos
    See Also:
    This method will load datasets from CKAN Organizations that are in "bureau_reference_data.json" organization. The file path parameter will be the temp location for the CKAN downloads. To produce a fresh downloand, this filepath must be renamed.

      • updateDataset

        public Dataset updateDataset(Dataset updateDS)
                      throws org.json.simple.parser.ParseException,
                             java.io.IOException,
                             DatasetException
        This method takes in a dataset and updates it on CKAN. Lots of issues with this method because of id=title of the dataset. One approach is to search on the title, grab the CKAN id and then do a another call to update the dataset.

      • loadOrganizationsIntoCatalog

        public Catalog loadOrganizationsIntoCatalog(java.lang.String downloadFilePath)
                                     throws CatalogException,
                                            java.io.IOException
        This method uses file "bureau_reference_data.json" to load list of bureaus with their corresponding CKAN organization identifier. It will first look to see if ckan// exists. If the file does not exist, it will go to CKAN server to retrieve it. If the file exists, this method will load the existing file into a string.
        Parameters:
        downloadFilePath -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        CatalogException
        java.io.IOException
